cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with cutting problems on surface-embedded graphs, which are a subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). The lower bounds are based on the Exponential Time Hypothesis (ETH), which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves graph algorithms (cs.DS) and parameterized complexity (cs.DM), as well as some combinatorial aspects (cs.GT).
